org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.json.jackson.datavalues

Class JacksonValueMonolingualText

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.json.jackson.datavalues.JacksonValue
      • org.wikidata.wdtk.datamodel.json.jackson.datavalues.JacksonValueMonolingualText
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MonolingualTextValue, Value

    public class JacksonValueMonolingualText
extends JacksonValue
implements MonolingualTextValue
    Jackson implementation of MonolingualTextValue. Java attributes are named equally to the JSON fields. Deviations are due to different naming in the implemented interfaces. The "value" in this JSON context is called "text".

    The class extends JacksonValue which adds a type association done by the JSON.

    Author:
    Fredo Erxleben
